The paper deals with deep learning-based semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of self-ensembling, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with data augmentation, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM).
